How to create a pull request

1. Create commit about an issue

2. Fetch last version of upstream

> git fetch upstream

3. Checkout and branch wip-1.0 upstream branch

> git checkout -b upstream upstream/wip-1.0

4. Merge last commit with local upstream branch

> git cherry-pick <SHA-1>

5. Push my changes to github

> git push origin upstream

6. Open a pull request on github
